00:29:00,625 --> 00:29:03,669
Master Winslow, there must be
something about the blue moon

488
00:29:03,745 --> 00:29:05,306
on your magic window machine.

489
00:29:05,505 --> 00:29:08,070
Just what is this magic searching device?

490
00:29:08,346 --> 00:29:09,830
Right now, I'm using Google.

491
00:29:11,746 --> 00:29:13,633
- Google.
- Google.

492
00:29:15,986 --> 00:29:20,754
Okay. "Blue moon.
A full moon that occurs twice in one month.

493
00:29:20,826 --> 00:29:22,431
"A figurative construct..."

494
00:29:22,826 --> 00:29:24,354
- Much like yourselves.
- Hey!

495
00:29:24,426 --> 00:29:27,110
"But the moon itself
doesn't appear to be blue."

496
00:29:27,267 --> 00:29:28,467
- What?
- Not blue?

497
00:29:28,546 --> 00:29:30,194
- Perfect!
- Now we'll never get home!

498
00:29:30,267 --> 00:29:34,151
No cause for alarm, my little Smurfs.
If we're to open the portal home,

499
00:29:34,227 --> 00:29:35,994
I'll just have to smurf us a potion

500
00:29:36,066 --> 00:29:37,387
to invoke the blue moon.

501
00:29:37,466 --> 00:29:38,754
You hear that, honey?

502
00:29:38,826 --> 00:29:41,150
They're only staying till
an actual blue moon rises.

503
00:29:41,426 --> 00:29:44,635
Which could happen if the little blue
Santa man makes a magic potion,

504
00:29:44,707 --> 00:29:47,314
which, at this point,
seems completely plausible.

505
00:29:47,387 --> 00:29:48,992
- Want a bite?
- No, thank you.

506
00:29:49,067 --> 00:29:52,636
Of course, the stars will
need to be perfectly aligned.

507
00:29:52,707 --> 00:29:56,995
And when that might be is hard to determine
without the proper instrument.

508
00:29:57,507 --> 00:29:59,788
Master Winslow,
might I borrow your stargazer?

509
00:29:59,868 --> 00:30:00,915
My what-whatzer?

510
00:30:01,788 --> 00:30:03,708
He doesn't have a Stargazer. Do you?

511
00:30:03,787 --> 00:30:06,515
- This is all my fault.
- We're all gonna die.

512
00:30:06,588 --> 00:30:09,228
- We're all gonna die!
- Smurf out of it, scaredy-brains!

513
00:30:09,308 --> 00:30:10,716
- One Panicky Smurf is enough!
- Hey!

514
00:30:11,108 --> 00:30:14,709
Besides, Papa had a vision,
and everything turns out smurf y.

515
00:30:14,948 --> 00:30:16,149
Right, Papa?

516
00:30:18,508 --> 00:30:22,230
Yes, yes. It all turns out just fine.

517
00:30:26,308 --> 00:30:30,314
We must find this Smurf thief.
Stop your complaining.

518
00:30:30,388 --> 00:30:32,308
If I were a Smurf, where would I go?

519
00:30:32,589 --> 00:30:35,677
You there, you there. Fancy pants.
Have you seen any little blue men?

520
00:30:35,749 --> 00:30:38,193
- Absolutely. What price are we talking about?
- You're selling them?

521
00:30:38,269 --> 00:30:40,277
- Have you looked in the drawer, sweetie?
- Wait, what drawer?

522
00:30:40,349 --> 00:30:42,750
- In the kitchen, Lilly.
- Who is this Lilly?

523
00:30:42,830 --> 00:30:45,153
Are you kidding?
She's the hottest girl in my department.

524
00:30:45,229 --> 00:30:47,357
Please, please. Please, young woodsman.

525
00:30:47,429 --> 00:30:51,674
What does the temperature of this Lilly
have to do with the finding of Smurfs?

526
00:30:51,750 --> 00:30:54,238
- Take your meds, man.
- What?

527
00:30:55,510 --> 00:30:58,074
Is everyone in this realm completely insane?

528
00:31:00,910 --> 00:31:02,874
Thank the gods, a local wizard. Excellent.

529
00:31:03,190 --> 00:31:05,034
Pardon me, wise sir?

530
00:31:05,110 --> 00:31:07,271
By any chance, have you seen
any little blue men?

531
00:31:08,830 --> 00:31:10,435
They're everywhere!

532
00:31:10,750 --> 00:31:13,478
I knew it. I knew it!
I told you we were close, Azrael.

533
00:31:13,990 --> 00:31:15,070
I know.

534
00:31:15,390 --> 00:31:19,919
Now, just take one, everybody.
We have to make sure our smurf berries last.

535
00:31:19,991 --> 00:31:22,239
Great. We're gonna be here how long?

536
00:31:22,311 --> 00:31:24,712
Not long. First, we have to get a Stargazer.

537
00:31:24,830 --> 00:31:27,919
Next, find a book of spells
and then smurf a portal

538
00:31:27,991 --> 00:31:31,275
and we're home.
Very simple, my little Smurfs.

539
00:31:31,351 --> 00:31:32,912
Bye, Elway.

540
00:31:32,991 --> 00:31:35,195
Someone looks smurfalish!

541
00:31:35,271 --> 00:31:37,355
- Why you wearing a leash?
- It's a tie.

542
00:31:37,431 --> 00:31:39,592
- Does it keep your neck warm?
- No.

543
00:31:39,791 --> 00:31:43,239
Clearly, it functions as an aid in his craft,
like a blacksmith's apron.

544
00:31:43,312 --> 00:31:45,440
I wear it because it's what
everyone wears at work.

545
00:31:45,632 --> 00:31:47,552
What are you, you pasty giant?

546
00:31:47,632 --> 00:31:51,637
I try to get people to buy things
by analyzing market trend predictions.

547
00:31:51,712 --> 00:31:55,313
Predictions! He's a fortune teller.

548
00:31:55,392 --> 00:31:57,837
Look, I would love to explain
but I am super late. I gotta go.

549
00:31:57,912 --> 00:31:59,920
- I really don't have time for this.
- What?

550
00:32:00,272 --> 00:32:01,636
You had one outfit on,

551
00:32:01,712 --> 00:32:04,593
and now you're wearing something
completely different.

552
00:32:04,673 --> 00:32:05,916
- Yeah. It...
- Now, Smurfette,

553
00:32:05,992 --> 00:32:08,033
she probably got the other one dirty.

554
00:32:08,113 --> 00:32:09,880
- Let's not embarrass her.
- Sorry.

555
00:32:09,952 --> 00:32:12,233
Thanks for letting us stay in your mushroom,
Miss Grace.

556
00:32:12,313 --> 00:32:16,077
- It's really nice.
- Well, thank you. I'm glad you like it.

557
00:32:16,153 --> 00:32:20,681
I like our little mushroom, too. But you know,
somebody wants a bigger mushroom.

558
00:32:20,993 --> 00:32:23,481
But, then you'd be further apart.

559
00:32:23,634 --> 00:32:26,634
You said it, sister. Okay, I've gotta go.
I've got an appointment.

560
00:32:26,713 --> 00:32:28,318
I've got a baby on the way, so...

561
00:32:28,393 --> 00:32:31,602
Wait, wait. We can't just
leave them here alone, without an adult.

562
00:32:32,634 --> 00:32:34,794
I'm 546 years old.

563
00:32:34,874 --> 00:32:36,358
Of course you are.

564
00:32:36,433 --> 00:32:37,917
- They'll be fine. They'll be fine.
- All right.

565
00:32:37,994 --> 00:32:40,078
- Love you.
- Okay.

566
00:32:40,673 --> 00:32:41,962
- Bye. Bye.
- Bye, Grace! Goodbye.

567
00:32:42,033 --> 00:32:44,282
By the way, I wouldn't go anywhere
if I were you.

568
00:32:44,554 --> 00:32:45,634
Why not?

569
00:32:46,594 --> 00:32:49,999
Our world doesn't do well
with visitors from other places.

570
00:32:50,074 --> 00:32:51,722
I mean, look what happened to E.T.

571
00:32:52,674 --> 00:32:55,075
It's a movie. A moving picture.

572
00:32:55,435 --> 00:32:57,476
Book. Just stay, okay?

573
00:32:58,354 --> 00:33:01,562
Great. He's gone
and we still don't have a Stargazer.

574
00:33:01,635 --> 00:33:05,640
Wait a smurf. If he's a fortune teller,
he reads stars all the time.

575
00:33:05,715 --> 00:33:08,880
Ergo, it's at his place of business.

576
00:33:09,155 --> 00:33:10,639
Excellent work, Brainy.

577
00:33:10,715 --> 00:33:12,602
What are we waiting for? Let's ride.

578
00:33:12,675 --> 00:33:14,443
- Yeah, come on, guys.
- Hey, stop it.

579
00:33:14,516 --> 00:33:17,156
- Come on, Smurfs!
- Let's go get that Stargazer.

580
00:33:18,476 --> 00:33:20,516
- Surprise, surprise.
- Oh, no.

581
00:33:20,595 --> 00:33:24,120
Clumsy, I think it might be best

582
00:33:24,195 --> 00:33:26,204
if you stay here. You know?

583
00:33:26,475 --> 00:33:28,679
Smurf an eye on the mushroom.

584
00:33:32,756 --> 00:33:35,201
Yeah, that's what I was thinking.

585
00:33:35,716 --> 00:33:37,724
- This way, Smurfs!
- Let's follow Mr. Winslow.

586
00:33:37,796 --> 00:33:40,284
Well, I can smurf an eye on the mushroom.

587
00:33:40,356 --> 00:33:42,004
Smurf away!

588
00:33:42,077 --> 00:33:44,161
- Let's smurf this joint.
- Is he down there?

589
00:33:44,236 --> 00:33:45,404
- Taxi!
- Can you see him?

590
00:33:45,476 --> 00:33:47,800
Look, he's getting into
the mechanical wagon.

591
00:33:47,876 --> 00:33:49,317
- Oh, no.
- Clearly that distance is too great...

592
00:33:49,396 --> 00:33:51,961
- Off you go!
- No! Gutsy!

593
00:33:52,037 --> 00:33:53,881
Come on, Smurfs! Smurfabunga!

594
00:33:53,997 --> 00:33:55,677
Goodbye, blue world.

595
00:33:55,757 --> 00:33:57,405
Use your hat, you ninny!

596
00:33:57,637 --> 00:34:00,441
Couldn't we just have taken the stairs?

597
00:34:01,477 --> 00:34:02,841
- There we go.
- Not funny, Gutsy.

598
00:34:03,837 --> 00:34:05,801
- It was a little funny.
- Smurfs.

599
00:34:06,837 --> 00:34:08,801
We're stopping. Hold on tight.

600
00:34:08,877 --> 00:34:10,165
Not to me, Grouchy.

601
00:34:10,237 --> 00:34:12,638
Oh, did I do that? Sorry.

602
00:34:12,717 --> 00:34:14,726
- Keep the change.
- Thanks, man.

603
00:34:14,998 --> 00:34:17,322
Master Winslow, we really need your help.

604
00:34:17,397 --> 00:34:18,477
- Hey.
- Right here.

605
00:34:18,558 --> 00:34:19,682
What are you doing here?

606
00:34:19,758 --> 00:34:23,402
What part of "we need a Stargazer"
don't you understand, you numptie?

607
00:34:23,598 --> 00:34:27,003
- You can't be out in public.
- Who are you talking to?

608
00:34:27,158 --> 00:34:30,366
If we could just have a quick look around
in your predicting parlor...

609
00:34:30,438 --> 00:34:32,446
- We really wanna go home.
- Come on, man, I gotta go.

610
00:34:32,518 --> 00:34:34,559
- Fine. Just come here, come here.
- Please, please.

611
00:34:34,918 --> 00:34:36,206
All of you. Trust me.

612
00:34:36,519 --> 00:34:37,927
Careful. Hey, watch the smurf berries.

613
00:34:37,999 --> 00:34:40,322
I'm not going... Hey!

614
00:34:40,398 --> 00:34:42,439
- Be quiet.
- It's dark in here.

615
00:34:42,519 --> 00:34:43,807
All right, who smurf ed?

616
00:34:44,839 --> 00:34:46,563
Hey! Get your hand out of my kilt.

617
00:34:46,639 --> 00:34:49,366
- That's not my hand.
- Hey, ticklish.

618
00:34:51,959 --> 00:34:54,207
- Morning. Morning.
- Good morning, Mr. Winslow.

619
00:34:54,279 --> 00:34:56,199
- Congratulations on your promotion.
- Thank you.

620
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:58,288
I hope you guys like desk drawers,
because that's where...

621
00:34:58,359 --> 00:35:00,487
- You're late.
- Odile!

622
00:35:01,239 --> 00:35:02,319
You were in my office.

623
00:35:02,639 --> 00:35:05,279
It's my building,
and we have much work to do.

624
00:35:05,359 --> 00:35:08,403
The launch for Jouvenel is tomorrow night.
Is your concept ready?

625
00:35:08,480 --> 00:35:11,208
Close. I had a crazy morning.

626
00:35:11,600 --> 00:35:13,324
What are you doing?

627
00:35:13,439 --> 00:35:17,520
Nothing. I'm excited.
I'm excited about all the concept ideas.

628
00:35:17,600 --> 00:35:22,204
And hungry. Sorry. Hungry for its success.

629
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:23,760
Nervous energy.

630
00:35:23,841 --> 00:35:25,805
Nervous energy's what's going on up in here.

631
00:35:25,881 --> 00:35:27,048
- I like it.
- Yep.

632
00:35:27,240 --> 00:35:30,885
- The fear of failure is a fabulous motivator.
- True that.

633
00:35:31,641 --> 00:35:33,124
Hey! Stop it.

634
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:35,841
- Henri.
- Make it work.

635
00:35:36,121 --> 00:35:37,768
You have no idea.

636
00:35:38,081 --> 00:35:40,089
- What is this?
- Why did I get the armpit?

637
00:35:40,161 --> 00:35:43,566
- Stop pushing me.
- Go easy on the cologne tomorrow.

638
00:35:43,641 --> 00:35:45,441
Are you crazy?

639
00:35:45,521 --> 00:35:47,322
- You're gonna get me fired.
- My hair!

640
00:35:47,401 --> 00:35:50,522
I couldn't even breathe in there.
It smelled like the business end of a sheep.

641
00:35:50,602 --> 00:35:51,890
- I don't see a Stargazer.
- How you doing?

642
00:35:51,962 --> 00:35:55,726
I'm sorry, Master Winslow,
but we badly need to borrow your Stargazer.

643
00:35:55,802 --> 00:35:59,371
I don't have a Stargazer, okay?

644
00:35:59,442 --> 00:36:03,806
It's not something people of this century
just have, especially here.

645
00:36:03,882 --> 00:36:07,691
- Not happy.
- Now if you'll excuse me, I have to work.

646
00:36:08,242 --> 00:36:11,123
Well, perhaps we could sing
to help things along.

647
00:36:11,202 --> 00:36:14,367
And then we'll get the stargazer.
Come along, Smurfs.

648
00:36:14,442 --> 00:36:17,651
La la la la la la
Sing a happy song

649
00:36:18,322 --> 00:36:20,166
La la la la la la
Smurf the whole day long

650
00:36:21,122 --> 00:36:22,170
Stop.

651
00:36:22,243 --> 00:36:23,531
La la la la la la

652
00:36:23,643 --> 00:36:24,690
Stop!

653
00:36:24,762 --> 00:36:26,606
Sing a happy song

654
00:36:26,682 --> 00:36:29,651
Come on. None of you find that song
just the tiniest bit annoying?

655
00:36:29,723 --> 00:36:31,130
I find it annoying.

656
00:36:31,723 --> 00:36:33,927
Well, what do you sing at work?

657
00:36:34,003 --> 00:36:36,207
- I don't sing at work.
- What?

658
00:36:36,283 --> 00:36:38,203
- And you have to wear a leash.
- Harsh.

659
00:36:38,283 --> 00:36:40,444
I know. How about if we hum?

660
00:36:43,083 --> 00:36:44,131
Please stop humming.

661
00:36:50,563 --> 00:36:52,004
I need to hone my message here.

662
00:36:52,164 --> 00:36:53,288
I've got a message.

663
00:36:53,364 --> 00:36:57,052
"Always chew with your mouth closed."
Papa taught us that.

664
00:36:57,123 --> 00:36:58,924
That's good. You should use that.

665
00:36:59,004 --> 00:37:00,892
Or, "Dance and be happy."

666
00:37:00,964 --> 00:37:02,851
How about, "Grab life by the grapes"?

667
00:37:02,924 --> 00:37:05,892
- "Turn that frown upside down."
- "Always bet on blue."

668
00:37:05,964 --> 00:37:09,205
- "Have a smurf y day."
- "I kissed a Smurf and I liked it"?

669
00:37:10,044 --> 00:37:12,565
It's an embarrassment of riches.

670
00:37:12,644 --> 00:37:13,965
They're giving you gold here.

671
00:37:14,164 --> 00:37:15,932
- Thank you.
- Master Winslow,

672
00:37:16,005 --> 00:37:19,365
you'll know it's the right message
if it comes from the heart.

673
00:37:19,445 --> 00:37:20,689
- Right, Smurfs?
- Yeah.

674
00:37:20,765 --> 00:37:21,965
- You said it.
- Absolutely.

675
00:37:22,045 --> 00:37:24,173
- Of course.
- Welcome to my world.

676
00:37:28,765 --> 00:37:31,614
I love emerging dramatically
through the smoke.

677
00:37:33,405 --> 00:37:39,091
It makes... It makes me feel
so deliciously mysterious.

678
00:37:40,245 --> 00:37:43,334
Also, it gives the skin a wonderful glow.

679
00:37:43,526 --> 00:37:44,605
What?

680
00:37:44,806 --> 00:37:45,973
Where? Where?

681
00:37:47,486 --> 00:37:49,210
What?

682
00:37:51,486 --> 00:37:54,727
Curses! So close.

683
00:37:55,166 --> 00:37:56,770
What?

684
00:37:59,166 --> 00:38:01,654
Theirs is upside-down.

685
00:38:01,847 --> 00:38:04,968
Idiots. They painted it wrong. Come, Azrael.

686
00:38:06,006 --> 00:38:07,054
- Hi.
- Hello.

687
00:38:07,127 --> 00:38:08,131
What are you doing?

688
00:38:08,206 --> 00:38:10,455
Just greening things up a bit.

689
00:38:10,526 --> 00:38:14,095
That's so sweet. That's very sweet but,

690
00:38:14,167 --> 00:38:16,612
you know, I'm not so sure
this stuffs gonna grow out here.

691
00:38:16,687 --> 00:38:20,168
We'll see. Smurfs have a very blue thumb.

692
00:38:20,727 --> 00:38:22,211
So where is everybody else?

693
00:38:22,288 --> 00:38:23,848
They went to get a Stargazer

694
00:38:23,928 --> 00:38:26,132
so Papa can smurf a blue moon
to get us home.

695
00:38:26,207 --> 00:38:27,408
And they went without you?

696
00:38:27,488 --> 00:38:30,292
Yeah. I mean, who knows why?

697
00:38:32,848 --> 00:38:34,289
- Hey!
- Sorry!

698
00:38:34,688 --> 00:38:35,932
Why don't we come inside?

699
00:38:36,007 --> 00:38:38,735
- Smurfs, where are you?
- Make sure to demonstrate that

700
00:38:38,808 --> 00:38:40,772
this new anti-aging cream can make

701
00:38:41,208 --> 00:38:46,217
any woman look beautiful, young, vibrant.
It's almost magical.

702
00:38:46,289 --> 00:38:48,330
Astonishing, really.

703
00:38:51,648 --> 00:38:53,535
I see no transformation.

704
00:38:53,608 --> 00:38:55,889
- Your potion has no power.
- Excuse me?

705
00:38:55,969 --> 00:38:58,696
Well, she's still an eye-offending dogfish,
if you ask me.

706
00:38:58,769 --> 00:39:02,054
- Sir!
- This is my mother who you're speaking of.

707
00:39:02,329 --> 00:39:04,610
I'm so sorry. I didn't realize.

708
00:39:04,689 --> 00:39:06,249
How sad for you in 30 years.

709
00:39:06,849 --> 00:39:09,337
Henri, escort this lunatic out.

710
00:39:09,409 --> 00:39:10,610
- "Lunatic"?
- Security!

711
00:39:10,689 --> 00:39:13,210
I am the great and powerful Gargamel!

712
00:39:13,290 --> 00:39:17,098
"Lunatic." Could a lunatic do this?

713
00:39:17,250 --> 00:39:19,694
Alakazootiful!

714
00:39:33,770 --> 00:39:35,090
How did you do that?

715
00:39:35,251 --> 00:39:37,291
Yes, and seriously, me next.

716
00:39:37,490 --> 00:39:41,778
So sorry, but lunatics and great wizards
never reveal their secrets.

717
00:39:43,370 --> 00:39:46,414
Come, Azrael! Now, where are my Smurfs?

718
00:39:46,530 --> 00:39:48,091
No, no, no, no, no. Don't go.

719
00:39:48,970 --> 00:39:50,770
- I need to know what you just did.
- Not telling.

720
00:39:50,890 --> 00:39:53,934
Please, señor Can you do that again?

721
00:39:55,251 --> 00:39:57,619
You may attempt to persuade me.

722
00:39:59,291 --> 00:40:01,178
What is it that you desire?

723
00:40:01,931 --> 00:40:03,492
Riches?

724
00:40:04,732 --> 00:40:05,736
Fame?

725
00:40:07,011 --> 00:40:08,016
Fortune?

726
00:40:09,291 --> 00:40:10,612
With my help,

