- I just want to
- Savor

965
00:53:07,402 --> 00:53:08,449
- All her smurf berry
- Flavor

966
00:53:08,522 --> 00:53:10,726
So I smurf ed her just a little kiss
Like this

967
00:53:16,002 --> 00:53:18,403
- Check out Clumsy.
- Whoa, Clumsy.

968
00:53:18,482 --> 00:53:20,283
- You found your niche.
- Yeah!

969
00:53:20,362 --> 00:53:22,610
Clumsy, holdin' it down. Look at him go!

970
00:53:23,283 --> 00:53:24,571
- Come on, Gutsy!
- Here we go!

971
00:53:24,643 --> 00:53:27,404
Yay, Gutsy! Get down with your bad smurf!

972
00:53:27,482 --> 00:53:28,890
- Go, Gutsy!
- That's right.

973
00:53:30,403 --> 00:53:32,727
- Careful.
- Get your smurf on!

974
00:53:32,803 --> 00:53:34,244
- Gutsy!
- Nice!

975
00:53:34,323 --> 00:53:35,928
- Yeah!
- Thank you.

976
00:53:36,123 --> 00:53:37,606
That was rare.

977
00:53:56,524 --> 00:53:59,493
Hey, guys. How do you like my new dress?

978
00:54:00,604 --> 00:54:02,645
Whoa! Is there a draught in here?

979
00:54:02,724 --> 00:54:05,932
Oh, okay, that's not what I had in mind.

980
00:54:07,724 --> 00:54:09,208
Are you thinkin' what I'm thinkin'?

981
00:54:09,405 --> 00:54:10,813
Sorry, boys.

982
00:54:12,125 --> 00:54:14,329
Yeah, that cools the giblets.

983
00:54:14,404 --> 00:54:17,809
Nothin' like a cool breeze
through my Enchanted Forest.

984
00:54:23,925 --> 00:54:25,333
- It's approved.
- What?

985
00:54:25,405 --> 00:54:27,325
- She approved it. She approved the ad!
- She loved it?

986
00:54:27,405 --> 00:54:31,093
Well, she said "approved,"
so coming from her, that's love.

987
00:54:31,325 --> 00:54:32,646
Oh, my goodness!

988
00:54:32,726 --> 00:54:34,134
- Patrick, yeah!
- You owned it!

989
00:54:34,325 --> 00:54:36,529
Oh, my goodness! Yay, Patrick!

990
00:54:37,325 --> 00:54:38,613
Yeah.

991
00:54:39,205 --> 00:54:41,289
No jumping, no jumping, no jumping.
No jumping, no jumping. Okay.

992
00:54:41,526 --> 00:54:43,927
- Should I send it? I'm not going to.
- Yes! Do it!

993
00:54:44,005 --> 00:54:45,129
- Do it this minute.
- I will do it. All right.

994
00:54:45,206 --> 00:54:46,854
Do it, do it.

995
00:54:46,926 --> 00:54:48,006
Go, go, go!

996
00:54:48,086 --> 00:54:50,607
Tomorrow this'll be on every billboard
in New York City.

997
00:54:50,726 --> 00:54:52,134
It's a go, laddie boy!

998
00:54:52,646 --> 00:54:55,527
- Well done, Master Winslow.
- Oh! Hey, guys, Papa's back.

999
00:54:55,606 --> 00:54:57,211
- Papa, are your calculations done?
- Yeah!

1000
00:54:57,486 --> 00:54:58,927
I'm nearly out of smurf berries.

1001
00:54:59,006 --> 00:55:02,214
It's proving more difficult than I'd hoped.

1002
00:55:02,446 --> 00:55:04,171
But we are going home, right?

1003
00:55:04,247 --> 00:55:07,171
Of course. Just not tonight.

1004
00:55:08,327 --> 00:55:09,735
Now, off to bed.

1005
00:55:13,887 --> 00:55:17,248
I was hoping I'd be sleeping
in my mushroom tonight.

1006
00:55:17,447 --> 00:55:19,172
I miss the other Smurfs.

1007
00:55:19,847 --> 00:55:21,211
Me, too.

1008
00:55:21,288 --> 00:55:23,688
I've never spent the night away
from home before.

1009
00:55:23,927 --> 00:55:28,095
Well, there was last night.
But who could sleep?

1010
00:55:29,928 --> 00:55:32,012
Hush. Hush now, Smurfs.

1011
00:55:33,288 --> 00:55:35,852
Everything's going to be just fine.

1012
00:55:36,208 --> 00:55:37,409
Papa?

1013
00:55:37,487 --> 00:55:41,775
Do you really believe we're ever gonna
get home to the other Smurfs?

1014
00:55:42,288 --> 00:55:43,651
Don't worry.

1015
00:55:43,728 --> 00:55:46,489
We'll be reunited with the others
soon enough.

1016
00:55:50,889 --> 00:55:53,933
If only the stars would align.

1017
00:56:02,328 --> 00:56:05,810
You know who I miss?
Chef Smurf. Hefty Smurf.

1018
00:56:05,929 --> 00:56:08,897
- Hey, Jokey Smurf.
- G reedy. Narrator.

1019
00:56:09,289 --> 00:56:11,854
- Painter. Baker.
- Harmony.

1020
00:56:11,929 --> 00:56:16,217
Oh, I miss Complimentary Smurf.
He always has such nice things to say.

1021
00:56:16,329 --> 00:56:19,330
I'll tell you who I don't miss,
Passive-Aggressive Smurf.

1022
00:56:19,410 --> 00:56:20,534
- Aye.
- Yeah.

1023
00:56:20,650 --> 00:56:24,010
He's always so nice,
but when he leaves you feel bad.

1024
00:56:25,010 --> 00:56:28,218
Ah, another wretched Smurf less night.

1025
00:56:28,850 --> 00:56:31,370
Oh, hello, little moth.

1026
00:56:31,450 --> 00:56:37,059
Perhaps with your help
I'll find a way to get them back.

1027
00:56:37,770 --> 00:56:41,175
Oh, you and I are kindred spirits, little one.

1028
00:56:41,690 --> 00:56:43,654
Both of us meant to soar.

1029
00:56:43,730 --> 00:56:48,531
Go now, and bring back an army
of mighty eagles to free me.

1030
00:56:49,051 --> 00:56:52,499
Fly, tiny eagle.
Fly and bring back your brethren.

1031
00:56:52,650 --> 00:56:54,734
Fly! Fly!

1032
00:56:55,051 --> 00:56:56,372
Fly!

1033
00:57:00,811 --> 00:57:03,855
Okay. Let's see here.

1034
00:57:03,931 --> 00:57:05,011
Hey.

1035
00:57:05,611 --> 00:57:07,292
I'm guessing you have
a long night ahead of you.

1036
00:57:08,491 --> 00:57:11,612
- You guys drink coffee?
- Is a Smurf's butt blue?

1037
00:57:13,651 --> 00:57:19,140
So tell me, that weird guy
in the ratty bathrobe at the toy store?

1038
00:57:19,212 --> 00:57:21,852
- Gargamel?
- He's not really a wizard, is he?

1039
00:57:21,972 --> 00:57:25,857
Not the smartest of sorcerers,
but dangerous just the same.

1040
00:57:26,572 --> 00:57:27,696
Thank you.

1041
00:57:28,852 --> 00:57:32,376
Back home, I could hold him at bay
with a spell or two.

1042
00:57:32,572 --> 00:57:35,060
But here, without my books and potions...

1043
00:57:35,133 --> 00:57:39,694
Well, today we got lucky.
But next time, who knows?

1044
00:57:40,013 --> 00:57:41,137
Well, what are you gonna do?

1045
00:57:41,332 --> 00:57:45,293
I'll do anything and everything I can do
to get my Smurfs home.

1046
00:57:46,013 --> 00:57:49,178
I won't ever give up. They're my family.

1047
00:57:49,653 --> 00:57:52,021
And you never give up on family.

1048
00:57:55,533 --> 00:57:58,414
Doesn't it freak you out sometimes

1049
00:57:59,134 --> 00:58:02,178
having all those little guys
depending on you?

1050
00:58:03,534 --> 00:58:05,782
I mean, what if you screw up?

1051
00:58:06,733 --> 00:58:08,578
How'd you know when you were ready?

1052
00:58:08,974 --> 00:58:11,135
Here. Come sit on Papa's lap.

1053
00:58:13,294 --> 00:58:15,334
Yeah, right. Scratch that.

1054
00:58:15,414 --> 00:58:17,979
- Probably not the best idea.
- Yeah, yeah.

1055
00:58:18,094 --> 00:58:19,458
Let me ask you something.

1056
00:58:20,054 --> 00:58:23,055
Why did you come for us today
when your Grace called?

1057
00:58:23,535 --> 00:58:26,416
She needed me. I could hear it in her voice.

1058
00:58:28,495 --> 00:58:30,699
Well, that's what being a papa is.

1059
00:58:30,775 --> 00:58:33,143
When it comes time, you just do.

1060
00:58:34,575 --> 00:58:37,695
And knowing what to do
doesn't come from up here.

1061
00:58:41,055 --> 00:58:44,536
It comes from here, where it matters most.

1062
00:58:45,695 --> 00:58:47,223
My spleen?

1063
00:58:47,296 --> 00:58:49,500
No, your heart.

1064
00:58:49,616 --> 00:58:53,784
I'm trying to have a moment here,
you whippersnapper.

1065
00:58:57,656 --> 00:59:01,300
- You're a good papa, Papa.
- And you'll be a good one, too.

1066
00:59:18,777 --> 00:59:20,621
Come on, what you doing, man?
Get that weight off there.

1067
00:59:20,697 --> 00:59:22,901
Come on, baby, stop playing.

1068
00:59:24,216 --> 00:59:27,217
Come on, you silly moth.
Where are my eagles?

1069
00:59:28,176 --> 00:59:30,261
You know what happens to people
who sit on my bench?

1070
00:59:30,897 --> 00:59:32,185
Be gone with you, behemoth,

1071
00:59:32,697 --> 00:59:36,865
for I have instructed a moth
to summon forth a gaggle of noble eagles

1072
00:59:36,977 --> 00:59:38,625
to free me from this confine.

1073
00:59:39,378 --> 00:59:40,818
- Get up, Grandpa!
- Hey.

1074
00:59:41,817 --> 00:59:43,662
You see? You see?

1075
00:59:43,738 --> 00:59:47,066
The dungeon isn't built that can hold
the likes of Gargamel.

1076
00:59:47,218 --> 00:59:52,347
Behold my glorious army of... Flies?

1077
00:59:52,418 --> 00:59:54,983
- Flies? I Said "to fly." "Fly."
- What is this?

1078
00:59:55,058 --> 00:59:58,582
Not "flies," you light-loving moron.

1079
00:59:59,538 --> 01:00:01,622
All right, up, up, up, bother it all.

1080
01:00:01,778 --> 01:00:05,063
Up! Up, you inglorious devils!

1081
01:00:05,138 --> 01:00:07,267
So long, scallywags!

1082
01:00:09,859 --> 01:00:13,264
Well, don't do it again.
Go around it, go around!

1083
01:00:13,339 --> 01:00:16,547
- Oh, that's nasty.
- Go around it. Stupid flies.

1084
01:00:16,738 --> 01:00:17,939
Wait, take me with you!

1085
01:00:18,019 --> 01:00:20,027
Wait! Wait!

1086
01:00:23,779 --> 01:00:26,267
To my castle for more essence!

1087
01:00:36,899 --> 01:00:38,340
Here they come, here they come.

1088
01:00:41,660 --> 01:00:44,345
- Pretty smurf y, if I do say so myself.
- Yeah.

1089
01:00:44,420 --> 01:00:47,301
Come on, Elway, right over here.
Good boy. Thank you very much.

1090
01:00:47,380 --> 01:00:49,180
- Oh, my goodness.
- Here we go.

1091
01:00:49,940 --> 01:00:52,188
- There we are.
- Clumsy.

1092
01:00:52,260 --> 01:00:55,620
- Blue thumbs.
- This is unbelievable.

1093
01:00:55,700 --> 01:00:57,064
I think there's too much pink.

1094
01:00:57,141 --> 01:01:00,425
Just because your name is Grouchy
doesn't mean you always have to be grouchy.

1095
01:01:00,500 --> 01:01:01,788
Yeah, it does.

1096
01:01:01,860 --> 01:01:03,181
- Smurfette.
- Hi.

1097
01:01:03,261 --> 01:01:06,545
- High five. High four.
- High four.

1098
01:01:06,621 --> 01:01:11,946
Great news! The stars have revealed
a perfect time to smurf the blue moon.

1099
01:01:13,501 --> 01:01:15,661
- We're going home! Yay!
- I knew you'd do it, Papa!

1100
01:01:15,741 --> 01:01:17,421
- All right!
- Smurftastic!

1101
01:01:17,501 --> 01:01:19,029
I never doubted it for a second.

1102
01:01:19,102 --> 01:01:22,986
It has to be done tonight,
between first star and high moon.

1103
01:01:23,141 --> 01:01:24,941
That's our only chance.

1104
01:01:25,021 --> 01:01:27,902
But we'll need a magic spell
that works in this realm

1105
01:01:28,022 --> 01:01:29,909
to open the portal home.

1106
01:01:29,981 --> 01:01:33,026
- Master Winslow, a question, please.
- Yeah, shoot.

1107
01:01:33,142 --> 01:01:35,302
Is there a place that sells spells?

1108
01:01:35,382 --> 01:01:36,583
No.

1109
01:01:36,702 --> 01:01:40,030
- Is there a place that proffers potions?
- Yeah, no.

1110
01:01:40,382 --> 01:01:42,269
How about old books?

1111
01:01:42,582 --> 01:01:44,950
Wait, there's an antique book shop
right near where I work.

1112
01:01:45,023 --> 01:01:46,823
- Yes. Dr. Wong's. Yeah.
- Dr. Wong's something.

1113
01:01:46,902 --> 01:01:50,427
- Perfect. That'll do.
- Oh, hear that, boys? We're almost home.

1114
01:01:50,503 --> 01:01:52,347
- Yeah!
- I love being almost home.

1115
01:01:52,423 --> 01:01:54,343
Hey! Smurf hug!

1116
01:01:55,863 --> 01:01:57,631
Oh, I love you guys!

1117
01:01:57,783 --> 01:01:59,191
Bring it in, big fella.

1118
01:01:59,263 --> 01:02:00,791
- I wouldn't...
- Come on, we know you want to.

1119
01:02:00,863 --> 01:02:01,987
- Yes.
- Yeah, come on, Patrick.

1120
01:02:02,103 --> 01:02:03,424
- If I can do it, you can do it.
- Go on, big fella.

1121
01:02:03,543 --> 01:02:04,951
- Here he comes!
- Smurf hug!

1122
01:02:05,023 --> 01:02:07,064
- We're goin' home!
- Hey there.

1123
01:02:13,463 --> 01:02:15,143
Hey, get up here.

1124
01:02:20,224 --> 01:02:22,712
- That's it, laddie. Nice one.
- What's that?

1125
01:02:22,783 --> 01:02:24,868
Yeah. All of ya. All of ya!

1126
01:02:25,184 --> 01:02:27,912
Oh, look!
We don't have to make a blue moon.

1127
01:02:28,024 --> 01:02:29,628
We've already got one.

1128
01:02:29,864 --> 01:02:31,185
- Really?
- What?

1129
01:02:31,264 --> 01:02:34,145
- Look, guys, right over there.
- No, it isn't.

1130
01:02:34,265 --> 01:02:36,752
It is. Smurfette's right.
Look at the blue moon.

1131
01:02:39,104 --> 01:02:41,308
That's the wrong ad.

1132
01:02:51,424 --> 01:02:52,548
What happened to my office?

1133
01:02:52,745 --> 01:02:55,746
We fixed it for the baby. Another smurf hug!

1134
01:02:55,865 --> 01:02:59,390
No. No, no, no. This isn't happening.
This isn't happening.

1135
01:03:01,225 --> 01:03:03,145
Someone sent this
to the ad agency last night.

1136
01:03:03,225 --> 01:03:04,785
- Who messed with my computer?
- I dunno.

1137
01:03:04,865 --> 01:03:07,549
- None of my Smurfs would...
- Wasn't me.

1138
01:03:10,785 --> 01:03:15,467
I Gargamel!, sorta, tripped.

1139
01:03:15,546 --> 01:03:17,947
Yeah, well, you Gargamel!, sorta,
just got me fired.

1140
01:03:18,266 --> 01:03:19,946
You sent the wrong file.

1141
01:03:20,026 --> 01:03:22,471
- Patrick, it was just an accident.
- What am I supposed to do, Grace?

1142
01:03:22,586 --> 01:03:24,986
You said that they would bring good luck.
This is anything but good.

1143
01:03:25,066 --> 01:03:27,434
I never should've let this happen.
I should've said no.

1144
01:03:27,546 --> 01:03:31,311
I never wanted a house
full of little people running around!

1145
01:03:34,946 --> 01:03:36,671
Blue. Little blue...

1146
01:03:36,867 --> 01:03:37,991
Okay...

1147
01:03:39,107 --> 01:03:40,187
Patrick.

1148
01:03:42,306 --> 01:03:43,430
What are you doing?

1149
01:03:43,547 --> 01:03:45,194
Going to try to save my job.

1150
01:03:45,307 --> 01:03:48,035
We never intended to be a burden,
Master Winslow.

1151
01:03:48,107 --> 01:03:49,907
I'm smurfilly sorry about what I...

1152
01:03:49,987 --> 01:03:53,871
Stop saying "smurf" for everything.
What does that even mean? Smurf!

1153
01:03:54,267 --> 01:03:55,555
Smurfitty-smurf-smurf-smurf!

1154
01:03:55,627 --> 01:03:58,912
There's no call
for that kind of language, laddie.

1155
01:03:59,067 --> 01:04:00,027
See?

1156
01:04:00,547 --> 01:04:01,868
Okay, Patrick, wait.

1157
01:04:03,148 --> 01:04:04,828
- Hey, hey!
- Will you...

1158
01:04:04,908 --> 01:04:06,588
- Wait, Patrick.
- Maybe I can try to fix it.

1159
01:04:06,668 --> 01:04:07,956
Just stop and listen to me
for a second, please.

1160
01:04:08,028 --> 01:04:10,832
- What?
- Look, I'm really sorry about your job, okay?

1161
01:04:10,908 --> 01:04:12,872
And I hope that you can straighten that out.

1162
01:04:12,988 --> 01:04:15,269
But you are so not seeing
the big picture here.

1163
01:04:16,029 --> 01:04:19,389
I mean, look around.
Look what's happening right now.

1164
01:04:19,589 --> 01:04:20,713
Of all the people on the planet,

1165
01:04:20,829 --> 01:04:23,109
those magical little creatures came to us.

1166
01:04:23,228 --> 01:04:24,833
They chose us.

1167
01:04:25,508 --> 01:04:28,913
Don't you see
how absolutely amazing that is?

1168
01:04:29,189 --> 01:04:31,350
This is a once-in-a-lifetime thing, Patrick.

1169
01:04:31,429 --> 01:04:33,349
This is our blue moon.

1170
01:04:34,829 --> 01:04:37,950
And if you don't stop
for just a second to see that,

1171
01:04:38,189 --> 01:04:39,553
you're gonna miss it.

1172
01:04:47,550 --> 01:04:49,154
Hey, hey. Taxi!

1173
01:04:50,030 --> 01:04:52,911
Come on! Come on! Blast. Blast you!

1174
01:04:53,150 --> 01:04:56,194
There's got to be some essence
in here somewhere!

1175
01:04:56,830 --> 01:04:58,118
NOT DOW.

1176
01:04:58,350 --> 01:04:59,758
What? What?

1177
01:05:04,710 --> 01:05:08,235
Very, very well done, my little friend.

1178
01:05:09,350 --> 01:05:12,199
And to think, I almost ate you that time.

1179
01:05:13,631 --> 01:05:18,040
Come, Azrael. We must find this Patrick,
the rouge merchant.

1180
01:05:18,271 --> 01:05:21,479
He will lead us to our
elusive little blue quarry.

1181
01:05:21,711 --> 01:05:25,356
Don't you just have a switch or something
to shut them off?

1182
01:05:25,471 --> 01:05:27,195
Tomorrow? Are you kidding me?

1183
01:05:27,271 --> 01:05:30,752
Ron, Ron. If I don't get those ads down now,
I don't have a job tomorrow.

1184
01:06:02,433 --> 01:06:03,916
Smurf me.

1185
01:06:50,354 --> 01:06:51,958
Which way to the bookstore, Brainy?

1186
01:06:52,034 --> 01:06:53,082
According to the searching device,

1187
01:06:53,154 --> 01:06:55,283
we take the F machine
two dots past the red circle to Chinaland.

1188
01:06:55,395 --> 01:06:57,556
- Look out, Brainy.
- "Chinatown," birdbrain.

1189
01:06:57,634 --> 01:06:58,801
- Smurftito, smurftato.
- Here it is.

1190
01:06:58,915 --> 01:06:59,919
- Come on, everybody.
- Let's go, let's go.

1191
01:07:00,035 --> 01:07:01,715
- Mind the gap.
- Wait? Are we sure about this?

1192
01:07:01,795 --> 01:07:02,996
- What?
- Jump!

1193
01:07:03,075 --> 01:07:04,843
- Oh, my.
- Not happy.

1194
01:07:06,675 --> 01:07:09,043
Come on, Brainy_
Let's poke around this great steel carriage.

1195
01:07:09,155 --> 01:07:11,283
- Is it safe?
- Of course it is.

1196
01:07:14,515 --> 01:07:16,043
That was great.

1197
01:07:17,035 --> 01:07:19,643
I hope we find this place soon.
I can't see out of this...

1198
01:07:21,515 --> 01:07:22,683
For smurf's sake.

1199
01:07:22,755 --> 01:07:24,884
I thought that's why we left Clumsy behind.

1200
01:07:24,996 --> 01:07:26,197
Oh, it smells like butter in here.

1201
01:07:26,275 --> 01:07:28,120
Where do you suppose
this magic bookstore could be?

1202
01:07:28,195 --> 01:07:29,800
- Wait a minute.
- There it is.

1203
01:07:30,036 --> 01:07:31,237
- It's closed.
- Figures.

1204
01:07:31,476 --> 01:07:33,680
We have to find a way in. Come on.

1205
01:07:40,036 --> 01:07:41,716
I'm gettin' too old for this.

1206
01:07:42,756 --> 01:07:43,957
- Brainy.
- Gutsy.

1207
01:07:44,036 --> 01:07:45,204
All right, everybody.

1208
01:07:45,317 --> 01:07:46,364
- Hey.
- Wow.

1209
01:07:46,436 --> 01:07:47,483
This place looks creepy to me.

1210
01:07:47,556 --> 01:07:49,324
It's not creepy, it's different. And I like it.

1211
01:07:49,397 --> 01:07:51,601
Let's just get the book
and get outta here.

1212
01:07:51,717 --> 01:07:55,002
You're right. This book of spells
is our ticket home.

1213
01:07:56,837 --> 01:08:01,879
I am but a simple wizard with a simple desire,
limitless power and world adulation.

1214
01:08:02,037 --> 01:08:05,006
Now why does it have to be so hard?

1215
01:08:10,518 --> 01:08:13,965
Pardon me. Please, wise sir.
Wise sir. Please, please.

1216
01:08:14,118 --> 01:08:16,519
Wherever did you hear
that ear-damning squall?

1217
01:08:16,678 --> 01:08:17,758
It's your little blue men.

1218
01:08:17,837 --> 01:08:20,041
I saw them going into the bookstore
around the corner.

1219
01:08:22,478 --> 01:08:24,726
You know, that song is really annoying.

1220
01:08:25,518 --> 01:08:27,886
Cautiously excited.

1221
01:08:29,398 --> 01:08:32,202
That's not it. That's not it.
Hey! Oh, no, that's not it.

1222
01:08:32,278 --> 01:08:34,843
Look at all these amazing books.
It's gotta be in here somewhere.

1223
01:08:34,959 --> 01:08:37,327
No, this isn't it.
You see anything, Smurfette?

1224
01:08:37,478 --> 01:08:40,719
Nothin' up here, guys. Look out below!

1225
01:08:41,158 --> 01:08:44,366
- I've got somethin', lads.
- Great job, Gutsy.

1226
01:08:44,439 --> 01:08:46,284
Oh. Nearly there.

1227
01:08:47,399 --> 01:08:51,884
- Well done.
- Just a minute. That's it. There we go.

1228
01:08:52,039 --> 01:08:53,240
Ah, yes.

1229
01:08:53,319 --> 01:08:55,567
"L'Histoire des Schtroumpfs. ”

1230
01:08:56,439 --> 01:08:57,803
Peyo.

1231
01:09:00,200 --> 01:09:02,284
- That's us.
- Yes, this is the one.

1232
01:09:03,880 --> 01:09:05,964
- Look at that.
- Wow.

1233
01:09:06,119 --> 01:09:07,724
Well, I'll be smurf ed.

1234
01:09:08,199 --> 01:09:10,687
The secret runes are hidden in the drawing.

1235
01:09:10,760 --> 01:09:12,288
You see all that in there?

1236
01:09:12,400 --> 01:09:14,965
Look here, at the patterns on this page.

1237
01:09:20,600 --> 01:09:22,520
Openous-lockicuss.

1238
01:09:29,320 --> 01:09:30,641
What?

1239
01:09:36,081 --> 01:09:40,565
You're right, Azrael.
This does have "me" written all over it.

1240
01:09:48,041 --> 01:09:50,923
Oh, that's just plain naughty.

1241
01:09:51,241 --> 01:09:56,206
All that remains now is to return
to the waterfall and invoke this spell, tonight.

1242
01:09:56,282 --> 01:09:58,802
- And we can go home?
- And we can go home.

1243
01:09:58,921 --> 01:10:00,930
- Oh, you're going home, all right.
- No.

1244
01:10:01,042 --> 01:10:04,850
To a little place I like to call
BellVeedaRay Castle,

1245
01:10:05,162 --> 01:10:08,763
where your essence shall finally be mine.

1246
01:10:09,362 --> 01:10:11,086
- The dragon wand.
- No!

1247
01:10:11,162 --> 01:10:12,242
It's...

1248
01:10:12,362 --> 01:10:14,042
Oh, please, please, allow me.

1249
01:10:15,483 --> 01:10:17,731
- It's Gargamel!
- Run, Smurfs!

1250
01:10:18,282 --> 01:10:19,603
- Come on, Smurfs!
- Go, go, go!

1251
01:10:19,723 --> 01:10:20,770
Wait for me!

1252
01:10:20,843 --> 01:10:22,851
- To the door!
- Smurfentine! Smurfentine!

1253
01:10:22,922 --> 01:10:24,810
- Hurry!
- Yes, yes, do resist, little Smurfs.

1254
01:10:24,883 --> 01:10:26,007
After all,

1255
01:10:26,123 --> 01:10:28,850
what is the hunt without the thrill!

1256
01:10:32,883 --> 01:10:34,007
No!

1257
01:10:42,443 --> 01:10:43,731
- We gotta go! Move!
- Run!

1258
01:10:43,803 --> 01:10:45,364
- Get goin', Smurfs!
- Faster, faster.

1259
01:10:45,484 --> 01:10:46,488
Let's get outta here.

1260
01:10:46,604 --> 01:10:50,172
Brainy, take the spell, brew the potion
and smurf the moon tonight.

1261
01:10:50,564 --> 01:10:51,688
It has to be tonight.

1262
01:10:51,764 --> 01:10:53,247
Me? Smurf the moon?

1263
01:10:53,324 --> 01:10:55,408
- No, no, I'm not ready.
- You have to be.

1264
01:10:56,644 --> 01:10:59,012
- Go. And no matter what happens...
- Papa?

1265
01:10:59,084 --> 01:11:00,612
- ...Do not come back for me.
- What?

1266
01:11:00,684 --> 01:11:01,928
- Papa, no!
- No!

1267
01:11:02,004 --> 01:11:04,208
- Papa!
- What are you waiting for, Gargamel?

1268
01:11:04,325 --> 01:11:06,605
Come to papa, Papa!

1269
01:11:07,764 --> 01:11:09,968
- Just go!
- Papa!

1270
01:11:10,085 --> 01:11:11,373
- Papa!
- No!

1271
01:11:11,445 --> 01:11:12,853
Keep movin', lass.

1272
01:11:13,004 --> 01:11:15,612
- Do as Papa said.
- Papa!

1273
01:11:16,164 --> 01:11:19,209
Is that all that you've got, Gargamel?

1274
01:11:30,885 --> 01:11:32,490
What's gonna happen to Papa?

1275
01:11:32,566 --> 01:11:36,407
Papa told us to smurf the moon,
and that's exactly what we're gonna do.

1276
01:11:36,806 --> 01:11:38,410
Come on. We don't have much time.

1277
01:11:38,606 --> 01:11:39,850
"Come on"? Come on, where?

1278
01:11:39,926 --> 01:11:42,130
How are we gonna get back to Clumsy?

1279
01:11:44,326 --> 01:11:46,607
We ride. Come on!

1280
01:11:47,606 --> 01:11:50,126
- Be still, bird.
- I don't think they're friendly.

1281
01:11:50,246 --> 01:11:52,210
- Well, neither am I.
- But they carry disease.

1282
01:11:52,966 --> 01:11:55,290
And Smurfs. Let's ride.

1283
01:11:55,406 --> 01:11:57,011
- Whoa, bird, whoa!
- Come on!

1284
01:11:57,127 --> 01:11:59,047
But I'm not sure I can do this.

1285
01:12:00,206 --> 01:12:02,487
You can do it, Brainy. Hold on!

1286
01:12:03,086 --> 01:12:06,251
According to my calculations,
this is dangerous!

1287
01:12:08,526 --> 01:12:10,087
It's getting dark.

1288
01:12:10,166 --> 01:12:12,971
Yeah. Yeah, I think
we'd better go look for them.

1289
01:12:13,046 --> 01:12:14,290
Yeah.

1290
01:12:17,687 --> 01:12:19,095
Hi.

1291
01:12:23,127 --> 01:12:26,936
- Where are the others?
- We think they're still at the bookstore.

1292
01:12:27,568 --> 01:12:30,132
Listen, Grace, I'm...

1293
01:12:35,248 --> 01:12:36,372
Hey, Odile.

1294
01:12:36,528 --> 01:12:38,776
Patrick...

1295
01:12:40,688 --> 01:12:42,892
Listen, listen. Before you fire me,

1296
01:12:42,968 --> 01:12:46,296
I know that the ads that ran
weren't the ads I sent.

1297
01:12:47,569 --> 01:12:50,657
But they're the ads I should have sent.

1298
01:12:51,448 --> 01:12:53,532
The ads I almost did send.

1299
01:12:53,928 --> 01:12:56,209
But I didn't 'cause...

1300
01:12:57,689 --> 01:12:59,053
I second-guessed myself.

1301
01:12:59,769 --> 01:13:04,974
I gave you what I thought you wanted,
instead of what I thought was right.

1302
01:13:07,129 --> 01:13:09,453
But this is right.

1303
01:13:09,810 --> 01:13:12,450
It means something to me and...
I don't know,

1304
01:13:12,529 --> 01:13:14,658
I think it's gonna mean
something to others, too.

1305
01:13:16,370 --> 01:13:21,378
It's not just a moon, Odile, it's a blue moon.

1306
01:13:22,169 --> 01:13:24,253
"Once in a blue moon."

1307
01:13:25,209 --> 01:13:29,651
That means that there are
only a few moments in your life

1308
01:13:29,810 --> 01:13:36,379
when something truly memorable,
truly magical, happens to you.

1309
01:13:37,651 --> 01:13:43,139
And, if you hesitate, if you're afraid,

1310
01:13:44,530 --> 01:13:46,091
you might just miss it.

1311
01:13:47,451 --> 01:13:49,654
That's what that image means.

1312
01:13:50,771 --> 01:13:54,612
Don't let those blue moon moments
pass you by.

1313
01:13:57,691 --> 01:14:00,856
I will call you back to tell you if you're fired.

1314
01:14:06,452 --> 01:14:08,536
I so smurf in' love you.

1315
01:14:11,372 --> 01:14:13,892
Left-left, right! Right-right, bird!

1316
01:14:13,972 --> 01:14:16,372
- Brace for impact!
- The window's open, ya ninny.

1317
01:14:17,932 --> 01:14:19,536
We're outta control!

1318
01:14:19,892 --> 01:14:22,140
Whoa, bird! Watch out for the...

1319
01:14:23,052 --> 01:14:24,820
- That'll do, pigeon.
- Thank you, bird.

1320
01:14:24,892 --> 01:14:26,660
Look! We got the incantation.

1321
01:14:26,772 --> 01:14:28,736
- Where's Papa?
- Gargamel's got him.

1322
01:14:28,852 --> 01:14:30,816
- What?
- Oh, no.

1323
01:14:30,973 --> 01:14:34,333
He took him to some place
called BellVeedaRay Castle.

1324
01:14:34,452 --> 01:14:37,180
- He's gonna...
- Don't say it.

1325
01:14:37,533 --> 01:14:39,420
BellVeedaRay. What is BellVeedaRay?

1326
01:14:39,532 --> 01:14:42,381
Belve... He's taken him
to Belvedere Castle in Central Park.

1327
01:14:42,453 --> 01:14:44,253
To extract his essence.

1328
01:14:44,373 --> 01:14:46,217
- What? Well, we have to go get him.
- Yeah.

1329
01:14:46,293 --> 01:14:48,421
No! Gargamel's more powerful than ever.

1330
01:14:48,533 --> 01:14:51,414
Papa said no matter what happens
we're not to go back for him.

1331
01:14:51,574 --> 01:14:52,894
He's trying to protect us.

1332
01:14:53,013 --> 01:14:56,374
- No! We can't leave Papa behind.
- It was a Smurf promise.

1333
01:14:56,494 --> 01:14:57,782
No, no, no. We can't.

1334
01:14:57,854 --> 01:15:00,702
We promised Papa
we'd do exactly what he said.

1335
01:15:00,813 --> 01:15:02,581
- That's right.
- I didn't.

1336
01:15:04,373 --> 01:15:06,141
I never promised him anything.

1337
01:15:06,413 --> 01:15:10,135
Neither did I. And there is no way
I'm leaving here without Papa.

1338
01:15:12,094 --> 01:15:14,582
Patrick, wait. I'm coming with you.

1339
01:15:17,934 --> 01:15:19,254
I'm in.

1340
01:15:22,774 --> 01:15:24,542
Aye. Me, too.

1341
01:15:26,614 --> 01:15:30,575
No Smurf left behind! Not Papa, and not you.

1342
01:15:31,415 --> 01:15:34,296
- All for one and one for Smurf!
- All for one and one for Smurf!

1343
01:15:39,455 --> 01:15:42,259
I 'll squeeze a few
And tweeze a few

1344
01:15:42,335 --> 01:15:44,703
And steal their essence blue

1345
01:15:47,776 --> 01:15:51,420
Very impressive, my dear, sweet little Papa!

1346
01:15:55,095 --> 01:15:56,820
Oh, look at this.

1347
01:15:57,336 --> 01:16:04,101
Just a tiny little bit of your little tiny beard
yields me all of this essence.

1348
01:16:04,896 --> 01:16:10,505
Just imagine what I'll be able to harvest
from your entire family of Smurfs.

1349
01:16:10,977 --> 01:16:12,657
Alakazookas!

1350
01:16:15,536 --> 01:16:19,584
Behold my glorious Smurf magic machine!

1351
01:16:23,257 --> 01:16:26,945
No. No! The cages! No! No!

1352
01:16:27,937 --> 01:16:31,418
I'll steam the essence from their sweat.
I'll tug it from their tears!

1353
01:16:31,617 --> 01:16:33,625
I'll snip it from their hair.

1354
01:16:34,777 --> 01:16:36,818
You're a fool, Gargamel.

1355
01:16:36,898 --> 01:16:39,779
My Smurfs are well on their way home
by now.

1356
01:17:04,059 --> 01:17:06,579
Oh, yeah. Let's light this candle.

1357
01:17:12,539 --> 01:17:14,187
Good luck, Gutsy!

1358
01:17:14,899 --> 01:17:18,304
- Into the breach!
- I'll see you there!

1359
01:17:28,379 --> 01:17:32,068
- We all remember the plan, right?
- Let's get our smurf on.

1360
01:17:32,540 --> 01:17:33,707
Brainy, what's happening?

1361
01:17:33,979 --> 01:17:37,668
I've added the ingredients.
It's more powerful than anticipated.

1362
01:17:37,780 --> 01:17:39,144
I don't think I can do it.

1363
01:17:39,260 --> 01:17:42,784
Okay, Brainy, you can do this.
Just say the incantation.

1364
01:17:59,061 --> 01:18:00,382
I'll be smurf ed!

1365
01:18:01,621 --> 01:18:05,309
I did it. I did it, Papa! I did it!

1366
01:18:08,661 --> 01:18:11,062
- I don't believe it!
- Wow.

1367
01:18:11,421 --> 01:18:13,985
- It's the Anjelou moon.
- How did she do that?

1368
01:18:14,581 --> 01:18:16,665
- It's beautiful.
- Oh, Odile.

1369
01:18:17,141 --> 01:18:19,629
- Oh, wow.
- That's wonderful.

1370
01:18:27,582 --> 01:18:29,786
Now, I don't want you to worry, Papa.

1371
01:18:29,862 --> 01:18:33,222
That which doesn't kill you
only makes me stronger.

1372
01:18:35,141 --> 01:18:36,669
- Yo!
- Huh?

1373
01:18:36,902 --> 01:18:39,270
Gargamel! Come out and play!

1374
01:18:39,422 --> 01:18:42,946
Oh, I think our tiny little guests
have finally arrived.

1375
01:18:43,262 --> 01:18:44,463
- No!
- Ah, well.

1376
01:18:44,542 --> 01:18:46,943
Enjoy the ride, Papa!

1377
01:18:48,543 --> 01:18:50,430
And remember, keep your hands and feet

1378
01:18:50,502 --> 01:18:53,426
- inside the cart at all times.
- No. No! No!

1379
01:18:53,503 --> 01:18:55,303
Smurfs, run!

1380
01:18:57,023 --> 01:18:58,627
Smurfs.

1381
01:19:04,023 --> 01:19:07,625
You have our Papa. Prepare to get smurf ed!

1382
01:19:07,743 --> 01:19:09,348
Yeah, what he said.

1383
01:19:09,463 --> 01:19:10,904
Adorable.

1384
01:19:10,983 --> 01:19:14,465
Two little smurfs come to save
their beloved Papa.

1385
01:19:14,783 --> 01:19:16,224
Hey, Gargamel.

1386
01:19:16,863 --> 01:19:19,548
Make that three little smurfs.

1387
01:19:23,464 --> 01:19:26,268
And I went home and got a few friends.

1388
01:19:46,464 --> 01:19:47,948
MY, my, my!

1389
01:19:48,745 --> 01:19:50,305
I think the whole village must be here.

1390
01:19:51,745 --> 01:19:56,186
Whatever will I do with all this essence?

1391
01:19:56,705 --> 01:19:58,026
On me, boys.

1392
01:19:59,545 --> 01:20:00,549
Fire!

1393
01:20:00,665 --> 01:20:02,913
Let's get this hoedown started!

1394
01:20:03,465 --> 01:20:06,389
There comes a time
when every Smurf must stand up...

1395
01:20:06,466 --> 01:20:07,546
Watch it, you little hoodlums!

1396
01:20:07,625 --> 01:20:10,866
For what is good and cute and blue
in the world.

1397
01:20:10,946 --> 01:20:14,547
And on this brisk New York night,
that time is now.

1398
01:20:14,626 --> 01:20:16,230
Hey! Seriously?

1399
01:20:16,346 --> 01:20:18,627
Sorry, it's kind of what I do.

1400
01:20:21,506 --> 01:20:22,947
Eat yolk, Gargamel!

1401
01:20:25,787 --> 01:20:27,270
Patrick, can you do it?

1402
01:20:27,386 --> 01:20:28,390
Go, go, go!

1403
01:20:28,746 --> 01:20:29,990
Hurry, they can't hold out for long.

1404
01:20:32,107 --> 01:20:36,592
You know, one bad apple
can ruin your whole day.

1405
01:20:39,067 --> 01:20:40,747
Full smurf ahead!

1406
01:20:41,027 --> 01:20:42,348
Come on!

1407
01:20:44,507 --> 01:20:47,311
Hey, Gargamel,
here's a little souvenir from the Big Apple.

1408
01:20:50,787 --> 01:20:53,068
- Out of the frying pan...
- And into the...

1409
01:20:53,307 --> 01:20:54,267
- Fire.
- Fire.

1410
01:20:54,347 --> 01:20:56,115
I'm too beautiful to die!

1411
01:21:05,988 --> 01:21:06,948
Oh, Papa.

1412
01:21:07,188 --> 01:21:08,956
No. No, Smurfette.

1413
01:21:09,028 --> 01:21:10,872
What did he do to you?

1414
01:21:10,948 --> 01:21:12,028
You shouldn't have come back for me.

1415
01:21:12,108 --> 01:21:14,028
Papa, I'm getting you out of here right now.

1416
01:21:18,388 --> 01:21:19,392
Smurfette!

1417
01:21:19,468 --> 01:21:21,356
Hang on, Papa, I'll be back.

1418
01:21:24,749 --> 01:21:25,993
Charge!

1419
01:21:26,068 --> 01:21:27,073
Get him!

1420
01:21:27,148 --> 01:21:28,196
Grab the wand!

1421
01:21:28,269 --> 01:21:29,436
- Goin' in!
- Go!

1422
01:21:32,629 --> 01:21:33,633
Bombs away!

1423
01:21:33,708 --> 01:21:36,076
- I'm going for a strike!
- Alakazam!

1424
01:21:37,549 --> 01:21:39,153
- Crikey.
- Look out, Gutsy!

1425
01:21:40,429 --> 01:21:41,749
Oh, ya blinkin' flip!

1426
01:21:44,950 --> 01:21:46,074
Hang on, Papa.

1427
01:21:49,550 --> 01:21:50,554
Onions!

1428
01:21:52,909 --> 01:21:54,033
Get back, cat.

1429
01:22:00,390 --> 01:22:01,591
Here, kitty, kitty...

1430
01:22:04,390 --> 01:22:05,514
Smurfette!

1431
01:22:08,150 --> 01:22:09,351
Looking for me?

1432
01:22:09,830 --> 01:22:11,314
Play time is over!

1433
01:22:11,791 --> 01:22:15,315
Behold the awesome power of me!

1434
01:22:43,832 --> 01:22:44,879
Smurfette?

1435
01:22:45,031 --> 01:22:46,515
Had enough, huh?

1436
01:22:46,832 --> 01:22:47,911
You're mine, kitty.

1437
01:22:51,592 --> 01:22:53,512
I'm done smurfing around.

1438
01:23:02,793 --> 01:23:04,921
You smurf ed with the wrong girl.

1439
01:23:08,953 --> 01:23:10,393
- I got you, Greedy.
- Oh, my cupcake!

1440
01:23:14,193 --> 01:23:15,601
What's happening, Papa?

1441
01:23:15,913 --> 01:23:16,873
No!

1442
01:23:17,993 --> 01:23:20,558
Gargamel!

1443
01:23:21,553 --> 01:23:24,238
Not so fast, goody blue-shoes.

1444
01:23:24,713 --> 01:23:26,154
Oh, Papa!

1445
01:23:27,593 --> 01:23:30,998
Now, it's time to break their little blue wills.

1446
01:23:31,433 --> 01:23:34,161
- No.
- Are you watching closely, Smurfs?

1447
01:23:34,474 --> 01:23:37,081
- Papa!
- Your beloved little Papa

1448
01:23:37,194 --> 01:23:40,402
is about to meet his little blue end.

1449
01:23:40,474 --> 01:23:41,478
No!

1450
01:23:41,554 --> 01:23:42,962
Upsy-daisy!

1451
01:23:43,114 --> 01:23:44,719
Oh, no. Papa!

1452
01:23:44,794 --> 01:23:45,842
Papa!

1453
01:23:49,674 --> 01:23:52,643
No! No!

1454
01:23:52,714 --> 01:23:53,762
You again!

1455
01:23:53,835 --> 01:23:54,959
Goodbye!

1456
01:23:55,995 --> 01:23:57,042
I'm really...

1457
01:23:57,515 --> 01:24:00,396
This ends here, this ends now!

1458
01:24:00,474 --> 01:24:02,199
Really going to enjoy this.

1459
01:24:02,475 --> 01:24:03,599
Gotcha!

1460
01:24:04,075 --> 01:24:05,603
Freedom!

1461
01:24:05,674 --> 01:24:07,158
Son of a smurf!

1462
01:24:07,355 --> 01:24:08,643
Come back here!

1463
01:24:08,715 --> 01:24:10,799
Go, Gutsy! Yeah!

1464
01:24:11,755 --> 01:24:14,395
Come back here right now with my wand!

1465
01:24:15,755 --> 01:24:17,720
Oh, no. Crikey.

1466
01:24:21,396 --> 01:24:23,437
I... I got it.

1467
01:24:23,756 --> 01:24:25,764
- Oh, dear.
- Clumsy.

1468
01:24:25,835 --> 01:24:29,120
- So this is how it ends.
- Our goose is cooked.

1469
01:24:31,676 --> 01:24:34,044
- This is not gonna be good.
- We're doomed.

1470
01:24:34,676 --> 01:24:36,400
I got it! I got it!

1471
01:24:37,676 --> 01:24:40,284
The vision's never been wrong.

1472
01:24:52,557 --> 01:24:53,845
I got it!

1473
01:24:55,637 --> 01:24:58,321
My wand! Give me back my wand!

1474
01:25:12,757 --> 01:25:14,001
How dare you!

1475
01:25:15,958 --> 01:25:19,766
How dare you defy the great and powerful...

1476
01:25:24,558 --> 01:25:25,605
Oh, my God.

1477
01:25:25,678 --> 01:25:27,282
Smurfs!

1478
01:25:31,759 --> 01:25:33,286
Are you dead?

1479
01:25:37,679 --> 01:25:39,840
- Nice one, Clumsy!
- Are you kidding me?

1480
01:25:39,918 --> 01:25:41,446
- Get up here, you!
- Yeah!

1481
01:25:42,159 --> 01:25:44,603
Bravo! Danke schön, Clumsy!

1482
01:25:45,279 --> 01:25:46,806
- Patrick.
- Hey.

1483
01:25:47,158 --> 01:25:50,486
Clumsy! Clumsy! Clumsy! Clumsy!

1484
01:25:53,199 --> 01:25:55,360
Clumsy, you're a hero.

1485
01:25:55,439 --> 01:25:56,606
I'm a hero?

1486
01:25:56,759 --> 01:25:57,883
Yeah. Yeah.

1487
01:25:58,319 --> 01:26:02,968
I'm a hero! I'm so sorry, guys.
Definitely killed the moment.

1488
01:26:03,639 --> 01:26:06,967
- Clumsy, you little mook, you.
- It's Papa.

1489
01:26:08,120 --> 01:26:10,324
I owe you an apology, Clumsy.

1490
01:26:10,680 --> 01:26:13,845
I believed more in a vision than I did in you.

1491
01:26:15,120 --> 01:26:16,888
I'm so proud of you, Clumsy.

1492
01:26:17,200 --> 01:26:18,640
Thanks, Papa.

1493
01:26:19,440 --> 01:26:21,841
I promised myself I wouldn't cry.

1494
01:26:22,080 --> 01:26:24,328
And now to get rid of this!

1495
01:26:29,601 --> 01:26:32,929
To the portal, everyone!
There's no time to spare.

1496
01:26:33,520 --> 01:26:35,604
- Smurf y'all later!
- Bye.

1497
01:26:37,841 --> 01:26:39,401
I'm not one for long goodbyes,

1498
01:26:39,481 --> 01:26:42,842
but I did smurf together a few words
I'd like to say.

1499
01:26:42,961 --> 01:26:44,009
- Bye.
- Take care.

1500
01:26:44,081 --> 01:26:47,169
I hated this. So much less than I expected.

1501
01:26:47,482 --> 01:26:51,006
- Bye, Grouchy.
- Don't get me wrong, I still hated it. Just less.

1502
01:26:51,121 --> 01:26:56,086
I'll not soon forget this place.
Especially not with these! Tallyho!

1503
01:26:56,642 --> 01:26:59,326
I shall be back, Broadway. Tootles!

1504
01:26:59,441 --> 01:27:01,209
- Hey, girlfriend.
- Wow.

1505
01:27:01,842 --> 01:27:04,003
I've never had a girlfriend before.

1506
01:27:06,082 --> 01:27:09,290
- I'll never forget you.
- Smurfette.

1507
01:27:10,482 --> 01:27:11,442
High four.

1508
01:27:13,403 --> 01:27:15,127
High four, Grace.

1509
01:27:16,403 --> 01:27:18,203
- Hey, Smurfette.
- And you.

1510
01:27:18,323 --> 01:27:20,287
- Hi.
- You, the little hero, come here.

1511
01:27:20,882 --> 01:27:22,803
Hero? Stop.

1512
01:27:23,442 --> 01:27:25,723
Well, actually, you mind saying
it one more time?

1513
01:27:25,843 --> 01:27:27,327
It's kinda got a nice ring to it.

1514
01:27:32,763 --> 01:27:35,764
- Bye, Grace.
- Well, Master Winslow, thank you.

1515
01:27:36,403 --> 01:27:38,323
- You saved me.
- So long!

1516
01:27:38,843 --> 01:27:40,404
You saved my whole family.

1517
01:27:40,603 --> 01:27:43,604
Actually I think it was the other way around.

1518
01:27:44,084 --> 01:27:47,925
Well, I should get going.
I've got a Smurf village to rebuild.

1519
01:27:48,244 --> 01:27:50,372
Your village has given me some ideas.

1520
01:27:51,604 --> 01:27:52,892
Come here.

1521
01:28:01,564 --> 01:28:03,047
Goodbye, Papa.

1522
01:28:03,764 --> 01:28:06,012
Goodbye, Papa.

1523
01:28:12,645 --> 01:28:14,173
Let's go home.

1524
01:28:17,204 --> 01:28:21,133
And so, the Smurfs left
the strange city of New York,

1525
01:28:21,685 --> 01:28:25,810
and I think they left it a little sweeter,
a little wiser,

1526
01:28:25,885 --> 01:28:28,013
a little smurfier.

1527
01:28:28,085 --> 01:28:30,650
And as that portal began to close
for the last time...

1528
01:28:30,725 --> 01:28:32,810
Hey! Seriously, stop!

1529
01:28:33,766 --> 01:28:35,610
Bye, New York!

1530
01:28:45,045 --> 01:28:47,130
It's Odile. Hey, Odile.

1531
01:28:47,206 --> 01:28:49,530
Patrick, I just called to say thank you.

1532
01:28:50,686 --> 01:28:52,890
Finally someone has given me what I want.

1533
01:29:00,406 --> 01:29:01,530
I think I'm not fired.

1534
01:29:02,886 --> 01:29:03,934
Wow!

1535
01:29:07,767 --> 01:29:11,215
Wow. So that's a new job, new baby,

1536
01:29:12,727 --> 01:29:14,736
some unique new friends...

1537
01:29:19,327 --> 01:29:21,411
- You know if you really want a bigger place.
- Bigger?

1538
01:29:21,768 --> 01:29:24,649
Are you crazy? Then we'll be further apart.

1539
01:29:30,008 --> 01:29:31,012
Grace,

1540
01:29:34,168 --> 01:29:35,456
I smurf you.

1541
01:31:29,692 --> 01:31:31,821
Smurfs. Smurfs!

1542
01:31:36,253 --> 01:31:39,177
I wish I could quit you. Get out of here.

1543
01:31:42,733 --> 01:31:44,413
What are you looking at?